# Formatting, Lint, and Type-Check

When creating or editing code, generated code, plans, JSON, YAML, Markdown, or other repository artifacts:

- Follow the repository Prettier configuration (`.prettierrc` and `.prettierignore`).
- Prefer running `npm run format` after broad formatting changes or when many files were generated.
- For focused edits, keep touched files compatible with `npm run format:check`.
- Do not manually reformat files that are ignored by `.prettierignore`.
- Before finishing substantive changes, ensure `npm run check` passes (`format:check`, `typecheck`, `lint`).

## Markdown

When creating or editing **`.md`** files (README, docs, changelogs, package notes):

- Treat Markdown as formatted source — do not leave MD-only edits failing Prettier.
- After touching one or a few files: `prettier --check "<path>"` or confirm root `npm run format:check` passes.
- After many MD edits (or MD mixed with code): `npm run format` from the repo root.
- For **`README.md`**: also follow [readme-footer.mdc](./readme-footer.mdc) (`#Col3:23` footer where that rule applies).
- Prose/layout (Prettier does not enforce all of this — keep it consistent):
  - Opening ` ``` ` on its own line (not after list markers or inline text).
  - Valid tables (header row, `|---|` separator, same column count per row).
  - Prefer markdown links for paths users should open.

**`.cursor/**` is in `.prettierignore`** (plans, skills, rules). When editing those Markdown files anyway, match Prettier manually (`printWidth: 120`, `tabWidth: 4`, trailing commas off) and keep the same structural conventions as above.
